  `us` → "American", `australia` → "Australian", etc.; `any`/`other` → omit
  the accent adjective).
- TIMBRE and MANNER words come from the character's personality (description),
  not the clip's sample sentence.
- Single comma-separated phrase, no period, no quotation marks.
- Do NOT use the character's name inside the descriptor.

The cast includes one entry named exactly `"Narrator"` — apply the same rules
to it. The Narrator's accent and demographics come from its assigned clip.

